1
00:00:18,894 --> 00:00:23,357
[ISAAK]
Mutter... Mutter.

2
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:27,653
[GIRL A]
Mutter.

3
00:00:33,742 --> 00:00:35,744
Huh? It's Mutter!

4
00:00:35,827 --> 00:00:36,912
Hallo, Mutter!

5
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:39,957
[CHILDREN chatter]

6
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,458
Mutter! Look here!

7
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:43,460
I did it, Mutter!

8
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:45,712
My darlings are all so clever.

9
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:48,840
Keep up the
good work, liebchens.

10
00:00:48,924 --> 00:00:50,342
[gasps]

11
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:51,885
Ja, Mutter.

12
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:52,970
[BOTH]
We promise!

13
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,555
I don't feel good.

14
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:55,597
[coughs]

15
00:00:55,681 --> 00:01:00,561
[CHILDREN coughing]

16
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:02,104
[RIZA gasps]

17
00:01:08,443 --> 00:01:11,071
[gasps]

18
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:15,909
[ISAAK]
Mutter.

19
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:29,631
[GIRL A]
I love you.

20
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:31,550
[BOY A, B]
I love you mutter.

21
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:43,645
[heartbeat]

22
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:48,317
[ISAAK]
Mutter.

23
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,278
[cries]

24
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:52,904
[RIZA gasps]

25
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:59,453
[grunts]

26
00:02:03,332 --> 00:02:04,499
[RIZA gasps]

27
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:13,800
[RIZA gasps]

28
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:26,313
[RIZA gasps]

29
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:30,651
[FEMALE NURSES gasp]

30
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:40,952
[RIZA gasps]

31
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,916
[RIZA gasps]

32
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,755
[RIZA gasps]

33
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:56,093
[ISAAK]
Mutter.

34
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:59,137
[RIZA]
No!

35
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:09,272
[footsteps]

36
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,362
[RIZA chuckles]

37
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:20,409
♪

38
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,960
[MAN A] What the hell is
going on in this town?

39
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:56,671
These cases are making
less and less sense.

40
00:04:56,755 --> 00:05:00,008
[MAN B] You can say that again.
Anything from forensics?

41
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:02,135
[MAN A] They say the blood
is definitely human,

42
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:04,346
and we're not talking
about a dozen people.

43
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:05,639
There's gotta be
enough blood here

44
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,557
for at least a
hundred murders.

45
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,100
But all the bodies
this blood came from

46
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:10,644
are nowhere to be found.

47
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:13,814
Almost as if they
had been... eaten.

48
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:16,274
[MAN C] So for now, the girl
we found at the scene

49
00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:17,818
is our only real lead?

50
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:20,695
[MAN A] Afraid so. She's got
a lot of questions to answer.

51
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:22,322
So keep an eye on her.

52
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:24,533
[MAN C]
And what about the other one?

53
00:05:24,616 --> 00:05:26,660
She said she didn't
know anything.

54
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,995
or the time being,
we'll let her rest.

55
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,498
But make sure to keep
an eye on that girl, too.

56
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,041
[MAN C]
Understood.

57
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,632
[LOTUS'S GRANDFATHER]
You ungrateful fool!

58
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:43,218
You'd rather be a soldier?

59
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:46,388
Don't you care about breaking
from our family's duty?

60
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:50,475
Murdering people? It's all
the same, either way.

61
00:05:50,559 --> 00:05:53,728
So, I'd rather take on a new
job that I can be proud of.

62
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:56,898
It's definitely preferable to
taking over a family business

63
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:58,316
like ours.

64
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,818
How dare you!

65
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:03,655
I hope you die out on the
battlefield, you pompous ass!

66
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:07,450
That was it. I've never
seen grandpa so mad.

67
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:09,494
So, I don't really have
anything to go back to

68
00:06:09,578 --> 00:06:11,079
when this is all over.

69
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:14,207
Well. I don't regret
my decision.

70
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,960
Now then, it's your
turn for story time.

71
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,044
[MICHAEL chuckles]

72
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:19,963
[LOTUS]
Tell me.

73
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:23,091
[LOTUS grunts]

74
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:25,886
[MICHAEL shouts]

75
00:06:30,984 --> 00:06:32,227
[LOTUS, MICHAEL]
Mein Kamaraden.

76
00:06:37,455 --> 00:06:38,582
[REN grunts]

77
00:06:47,591 --> 00:06:48,758
[REN grunts]

78
00:06:50,552 --> 00:06:52,137
[REN gasps]

79
00:06:56,683 --> 00:06:59,394
[door clatters]

80
00:07:01,313 --> 00:07:03,356
[REN]
Mm?

81
00:07:06,484 --> 00:07:09,613
What are you doing?
Just enjoying the view?

82
00:07:12,824 --> 00:07:14,910
You must be cold.

83
00:07:14,993 --> 00:07:18,288
Then again, I'm guessing you
probably don't get sick.

84
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:20,624
Was there something
you wanted to see?

85
00:07:20,707 --> 00:07:26,630
Oui. The roof. You said
how much you liked it.

86
00:07:26,713 --> 00:07:27,881
Did I?

87
00:07:30,634 --> 00:07:33,803
[MARIE]
You did. Don't you remember?

88
00:07:33,887 --> 00:07:36,389
The school roof is where
the group always met up.

89
00:07:36,473 --> 00:07:38,350
I'm getting some practice in.

90
00:07:38,433 --> 00:07:40,977
Then I'll be ready to
become the fifth member.

91
00:07:41,061 --> 00:07:43,188
I thought spending time here
would get me used to being

92
00:07:43,271 --> 00:07:44,064
up so high.

93
00:07:44,147 --> 00:07:45,315
[gasps]

94
00:07:45,398 --> 00:07:47,067
I wonder what kind
of conversations

95
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:48,526
we'll have on the roof.

96
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:51,696
What will we do, what new
things will we try together?

97
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:54,616
I'm getting excited
just thinking about it!

98
00:07:54,699 --> 00:07:57,535
I can't wait for us
to start having fun!

99
00:07:57,619 --> 00:08:00,205
This place is tres magnific, no?

100
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:05,001
You wanna be the
fifth member?

101
00:08:05,085 --> 00:08:07,212
Not sure we have
that number anymore.

102
00:08:07,295 --> 00:08:09,673
Why the hell didn't Honjou tell
me that the club was one of the

103
00:08:09,756 --> 00:08:14,511
swastikas when we talked?
There's no way she didn't know.

104
00:08:14,594 --> 00:08:17,555
Shirou must've
made her, but why?

105
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:20,517
Did she want to
kill herself? Idiot!

106
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,978
Because of that, they're both‐‐

107
00:08:23,061 --> 00:08:24,187
[MARIE]
It's okay.

108
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,355
[REN gasps]

109
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:29,192
They're both still alive.
I'm sure of it!

110
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:31,236
[REN chuckles]

111
00:08:31,319 --> 00:08:33,655
[REN] Oh yeah?
What makes you say that?

112
00:08:33,738 --> 00:08:35,365
Because I've come
to realize that

113
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:37,951
I've never really
seen you smiling.

114
00:08:38,034 --> 00:08:40,537
instead, you have
such a sad expression.

115
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:43,665
Almost always,
ever since we met.

116
00:08:43,748 --> 00:08:47,002
It hurts me to see you
looking so morose, Ren.

117
00:08:47,085 --> 00:08:51,423
It is as if you are telling me,
you wish we had never met.

118
00:08:55,051 --> 00:08:56,386
It's not that.

119
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:58,346
[MARIE]
So I made the decision,

120
00:08:58,430 --> 00:09:01,266
that I'd work hard
to make you happy.

121
00:09:01,349 --> 00:09:02,851
So please, don't worry.

122
00:09:02,934 --> 00:09:06,146
You can cheer up, Ren,
because nothing sad will happen.

123
00:09:06,229 --> 00:09:09,441
And if it starts to get that
way, I won't let it keep going.

124
00:09:09,524 --> 00:09:10,775
You see?

125
00:09:12,777 --> 00:09:15,280
[REN chuckles]
Yeah, you may be right.

126
00:09:15,363 --> 00:09:18,366
When something happens, I always
focus on all the bad parts.

127
00:09:18,450 --> 00:09:21,411
I mean, If Kasumi was able
to survive the attack,

128
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:23,538
maybe they were able
to survive it, too!

129
00:09:23,621 --> 00:09:26,583
Oui, try to look on
the bright side!

130
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:29,502
Listen, Ren, I've changed.

131
00:09:29,586 --> 00:09:32,547
I'm not the same as I
was when I first arrived.

132
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:35,842
It's strange to say that
about oneself, but I can tell.

133
00:09:35,925 --> 00:09:38,678
Ever since the golden one
skewered me through the chest,

134
00:09:38,762 --> 00:09:42,015
I've become something different.
Sort of like waking up.

135
00:09:43,767 --> 00:09:46,311
[MARIE] And since then it has
felt like I can understand you

136
00:09:46,394 --> 00:09:48,021
better than ever before.

137
00:09:48,104 --> 00:09:52,484
I can say the same about Kasumi,
as well as both Rea and Shirou.

138
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:54,944
Almost everyone I've met.

139
00:09:55,028 --> 00:09:57,822
I've had to deal with so much
sadness but there's happiness

140
00:09:57,906 --> 00:09:59,157
in there as well.

141
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:02,118
And that's the part that's
so dazzlingly bright.

142
00:10:02,202 --> 00:10:04,412
It's become dear to me.

143
00:10:04,496 --> 00:10:06,498
But, do you think
this change is bad?

144
00:10:06,581 --> 00:10:07,665
[REN]
Huh?

145
00:10:07,749 --> 00:10:09,209
Since it came from
something he did to me,

146
00:10:09,292 --> 00:10:13,254
do I need to throw it all away?
That would make me very sad.

147
00:10:13,338 --> 00:10:15,048
I'm afraid to lose it.

148
00:10:15,131 --> 00:10:16,633
No, Marie.

149
00:10:18,384 --> 00:10:21,638
[REN] It isn't something bad.
Hold on to it.

150
00:10:21,721 --> 00:10:23,723
I don't know what Reinhard
and Mercurius are thinking,

151
00:10:23,807 --> 00:10:26,059
or if what you feel has
anything to do with them.

152
00:10:26,142 --> 00:10:29,479
But what I do know, is that I
like you much better this way.

153
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:32,190
I want you to stay like this.

154
00:10:32,273 --> 00:10:34,734
So if what you're feeling
is important to you,

155
00:10:34,818 --> 00:10:37,445
then you shouldn't
doubt those instincts.

156
00:10:37,529 --> 00:10:40,115
What I want for us, is for
us both to never feel

157
00:10:40,198 --> 00:10:42,075
like we need to hide
who we really are.

158
00:10:42,158 --> 00:10:44,119
Do you remember
talking about that?

159
00:10:44,202 --> 00:10:46,913
I do, and you're right!

160
00:10:48,498 --> 00:10:50,959
I'll try, I promise to.

161
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:03,513
[footsteps]

162
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,017
[REN gasps]

163
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:12,772
[REN] So that's the
look you went with?

164
00:11:12,856 --> 00:11:13,898
[RIZA gasps]

165
00:11:15,275 --> 00:11:18,820
That outfit doesn't work
for you. Not in the least.

166
00:11:18,903 --> 00:11:24,993
[RIZA] The only one who
thinks that... is you, boy.

167
00:11:29,956 --> 00:11:32,834
Are you sure you really
wanna do this, sister?

168
00:11:32,917 --> 00:11:34,586
I'm not letting you through,

169
00:11:34,669 --> 00:11:37,672
so you should give
up now and go home.

170
00:11:37,755 --> 00:11:40,800
[RIZA] What about you?
Will you leave, Fujii?

171
00:11:40,884 --> 00:11:42,719
Why don't you take Kasumi
while you still can,

172
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:46,264
and run far from here? I cannot
let you take anyone else,

173
00:11:46,347 --> 00:11:48,141
but I can allow you to take her.

174
00:11:48,224 --> 00:11:50,977
[REN gasps]

175
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:52,478
We aren't going anywhere.

176
00:11:52,562 --> 00:11:55,231
So I suggest we try to
do this the easy way.

177
00:11:55,315 --> 00:11:56,649
For Rea's sake,

178
00:11:56,733 --> 00:12:00,111
I'm telling you to turn
around and get out of here!

179
00:12:00,195 --> 00:12:01,446
[RIZA gasps]

180
00:12:01,529 --> 00:12:03,531
What kind of world are you
going to leave for her?

181
00:12:03,615 --> 00:12:05,325
Do you honestly think
she'd be happy

182
00:12:05,408 --> 00:12:08,203
to have a killer in her family?

183
00:12:08,286 --> 00:12:11,372
[RIZA gasps]
Thank you, Fujii.

184
00:12:11,456 --> 00:12:13,625
I'm flattered you
think so highly of me,

185
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:17,629
und care about Rea.
But I fear I cannot.

186
00:12:19,214 --> 00:12:22,258
[RIZA] I cannot afford myself
the luxury of compassion.

187
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:26,346
To be kind, like you are.
This is the kind of woman I am.

188
00:12:26,429 --> 00:12:28,723
Rea knows, und expects
nothing more.

189
00:12:28,806 --> 00:12:33,686
She dislikes me at best.
Und I am frightened of her.

190
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:34,687
[REN gasps]

191
00:12:34,771 --> 00:12:36,105
Leonhart.

192
00:12:37,523 --> 00:12:39,067
[KEI shouts]

193
00:12:41,486 --> 00:12:43,238
[REN gasps]

194
00:12:43,321 --> 00:12:45,657
[RIZA]
Stall him for me, won't you?

195
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:48,368
I will open the swastika here.

196
00:12:48,451 --> 00:12:48,993
[REN gasps]

197
00:12:49,077 --> 00:12:50,620
Understood.

198
00:12:50,703 --> 00:12:51,829
[KEI shouts]

199
00:12:51,913 --> 00:12:54,582
You are naïve.
Und far too optimistic.

200
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:58,044
It's hard to believe you're
a descendant of Karl Krafft.

201
00:12:59,921 --> 00:13:03,258
For what it's worth, you were
a fine young man, Ren Fujii.

202
00:13:03,341 --> 00:13:06,052
But here, things will
end horribly for you.

203
00:13:06,135 --> 00:13:08,763
Whatever made you think I
would come here alone?

204
00:13:08,846 --> 00:13:10,932
You won't be able to
protect anyone like that.

205
00:13:11,015 --> 00:13:12,433
Hold on!

206
00:13:12,517 --> 00:13:15,019
Don't look to her, Fujii.
First you have to get past me.

207
00:13:15,103 --> 00:13:16,271
[REN grunts]

208
00:13:16,354 --> 00:13:17,772
[KEI] I'll fight with my
true strength this time,

209
00:13:17,855 --> 00:13:19,524
so that I don't bore you.

210
00:13:19,607 --> 00:13:20,942
Your true strength?

211
00:13:21,025 --> 00:13:24,445
Correct. Don't you
remember my tutoring?

212
00:13:24,529 --> 00:13:28,116
There are different levels of
ability based on our experience.

213
00:13:28,199 --> 00:13:31,160
First activity,
and then formation.

214
00:13:31,244 --> 00:13:33,830
Those are the only
levels you've achieved.

215
00:13:33,913 --> 00:13:35,665
But I rise above.

216
00:13:37,375 --> 00:13:41,087
Creation level.
Remake the rules.

217
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:42,463
The ability to form a world

218
00:13:42,547 --> 00:13:45,591
which realizes my
soul's desires.

219
00:13:45,675 --> 00:13:49,804
I decided, Fujii. That I
would never forget my vow,

220
00:13:49,887 --> 00:13:52,432
so my desire could
be made flesh.

221
00:13:52,515 --> 00:13:55,476
Like an eternal flame,
burning in memorium.

222
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:57,145
Creation!

223
00:14:00,315 --> 00:14:01,733
[gasps]

224
00:14:01,816 --> 00:14:04,986
[KEI] <i>Koko ni. Amatsukami no</i>
<i>mikoto mochite</i> .

225
00:14:05,069 --> 00:14:08,031
<i>Futoma</i> ‐ <i>ni uraete</i>
<i>noritamai tsuraku</i> !

226
00:14:09,949 --> 00:14:11,951
[REN grunts]

227
00:14:12,035 --> 00:14:12,952
[KEI]
It's useless.

228
00:14:13,036 --> 00:14:14,370
[REN gasps]

229
00:14:14,454 --> 00:14:17,165
Flames are unbreakable.
You can't cut through them.

230
00:14:17,248 --> 00:14:18,583
So...

231
00:14:19,792 --> 00:14:23,046
Now I've become them.
You can't stop me!

232
00:14:23,129 --> 00:14:24,172
[REN grunts]

233
00:14:28,343 --> 00:14:30,219
[gasps]

234
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:34,223
[screams]

235
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:35,058
[footsteps]

236
00:14:35,141 --> 00:14:36,309
[RIZA]
Who's there?

237
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:42,690
[VALERIA] Oh, so it seems
you've found me, then.

238
00:14:42,774 --> 00:14:46,027
It was my intention
to remain unseen.

239
00:14:46,110 --> 00:14:50,323
You aren't fooling anyone.
Despite all the noise outside,

240
00:14:50,406 --> 00:14:53,701
no one woke up, no one
took off in a panic.

241
00:14:53,785 --> 00:14:55,787
That was your doing, wasn't it?

242
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:58,247
I never asked you for
your help, though.

243
00:14:58,331 --> 00:15:00,625
Now, Riza, you wound me.

244
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:02,835
We've known each
other a long time.

245
00:15:02,919 --> 00:15:05,713
I think I know you better
than you give me credit for.

246
00:15:05,797 --> 00:15:07,715
Going around killing
hospital patients

247
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:10,885
while they flee in terror
isn't exactly your thing.

248
00:15:10,968 --> 00:15:15,223
No, it's not. But, if you'd
be so kind, please leave me.

249
00:15:15,306 --> 00:15:17,266
I'd prefer to not be
seen while working.

250
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,894
[VALERIA] You despise yourself
for being a murderer?

251
00:15:19,977 --> 00:15:23,773
Indeed, quite funny, isn't it?
Too little, too late.

252
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:26,943
But that's simply the way
I've always been, I suppose.

253
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:29,529
Wishing only to
bask in the drama.

254
00:15:29,612 --> 00:15:32,532
Somehow, gnawing guilt
makes me feel more complete.

255
00:15:32,615 --> 00:15:34,867
Is it because if you
forget about your doubts,

256
00:15:34,951 --> 00:15:38,079
you'll lose the last vestiges
of your humanity?

257
00:15:38,162 --> 00:15:40,957
[RIZA]
Perhaps. Much like you.

258
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:45,920
[RIZA] I don't want to kill,
but killing is a necessity.

259
00:15:46,003 --> 00:15:49,298
I will not waver from the
course I've been set on,

260
00:15:49,382 --> 00:15:52,051
but I want to continue
having that uncertainty.

261
00:15:52,135 --> 00:15:55,972
It's hypocritical and cowardly,
but at the very least,

262
00:15:56,055 --> 00:15:58,850
I can be thankful I
didn't end up like you.

263
00:16:00,685 --> 00:16:03,146
Riza. I must know.

264
00:16:03,229 --> 00:16:05,690
When you were pregnant,
who was the father?

265
00:16:05,773 --> 00:16:06,774
[RIZA gasps]

266
00:16:06,858 --> 00:16:09,110
You had two sons,
isn't that right?

267
00:16:09,193 --> 00:16:11,571
But you allowed one of
them to escape his fate.

268
00:16:11,654 --> 00:16:12,989
This much I know.

269
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:14,240
[RIZA gasps]

270
00:16:14,323 --> 00:16:16,909
[VALERIA]
In this dark drama.

271
00:16:16,993 --> 00:16:19,412
How did you come
to your decision?

272
00:16:19,495 --> 00:16:22,206
To sacrifice one son to
the black round table,

273
00:16:22,290 --> 00:16:25,084
and let the other
live as a human?

274
00:16:25,168 --> 00:16:27,587
Was he too much
like his father?

275
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:31,716
Did you fear the other
half of his blood?

276
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:35,052
Is it that very same fear
that continues to drive you

277
00:16:35,136 --> 00:16:37,138
to abandon Theresia?

278
00:16:37,221 --> 00:16:38,514
[RIZA grunts]

279
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:42,059
[RIZA]
That isn't your concern!

280
00:16:42,143 --> 00:16:44,812
Oh, but I think it
is indeed, Riza.

281
00:16:44,896 --> 00:16:47,857
I love young Theresia,
as you well know.

282
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:50,651
But I am uncertain as
to her exact origins.

283
00:16:50,735 --> 00:16:53,988
And so. I'm left to wonder
if this feeling can really

284
00:16:54,071 --> 00:16:55,781
be called my own love.

285
00:16:55,865 --> 00:16:58,868
Or, perhaps they're naught
more than the emotional stains

286
00:16:58,951 --> 00:17:01,287
clinging to the body I inhabit.

287
00:17:01,370 --> 00:17:04,540
[RIZA gasps]

288
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:07,293
[VALERIA] Thus, I wish
to find out for myself,

289
00:17:07,376 --> 00:17:10,171
and I know just how
to go about doing it.

290
00:17:10,254 --> 00:17:13,132
Because the other son,
the one who you freed,

291
00:17:13,216 --> 00:17:14,967
the one whose
happiness you longed for,

292
00:17:15,051 --> 00:17:16,844
just as any good
mother would.

293
00:17:16,928 --> 00:17:20,473
His bloodline continues here,
somewhere in Shambhala.

294
00:17:20,556 --> 00:17:21,682
[RIZA gasps]

295
00:17:21,766 --> 00:17:24,185
[VALERIA] By offering up
the scion of Johann,

296
00:17:24,268 --> 00:17:28,147
I can prove that my love for
Theresia is indeed my own.

297
00:17:28,231 --> 00:17:30,900
Perhaps prove that there's
more than borrowed emotions

298
00:17:30,983 --> 00:17:32,944
tugging on my heartstrings.

299
00:17:33,027 --> 00:17:35,655
The only way I can feel certain
that I am not driven by

300
00:17:35,738 --> 00:17:38,658
something so trivial, is by
putting a decisive end

301
00:17:38,741 --> 00:17:43,246
to Johann's bloodline, as proof
of my absolute devotion.

302
00:17:43,329 --> 00:17:50,419
By now you must know who it is,
without me having to say a word.

303
00:17:50,503 --> 00:17:52,964
[gasps
I've heard enough!

304
00:17:53,047 --> 00:17:56,133
I won't let you. I will
never let you do it!

305
00:17:56,217 --> 00:17:59,679
I chose to let Johann live!
I made my decision.

306
00:17:59,762 --> 00:18:02,723
I see, and you have chosen
for Theresia to die?

307
00:18:02,807 --> 00:18:05,601
[RIZA gasps]
That's right!

308
00:18:05,685 --> 00:18:10,231
I won't sit idly by. I won't
let you deny who I am!

309
00:18:10,314 --> 00:18:12,900
Your soul is fetid, Valeria.

310
00:18:12,984 --> 00:18:17,321
You accepted a monster's body...
so you could be strong!

311
00:18:17,405 --> 00:18:21,200
Of course. You are
no different, my dear Riza.

312
00:18:21,284 --> 00:18:23,661
Then I take it my
assumption was correct?

313
00:18:23,744 --> 00:18:26,747
You couldn't love Isaak because
he was too much like his father,

314
00:18:26,831 --> 00:18:30,251
but as a failure in that regard,
Johann could be loved.

315
00:18:30,334 --> 00:18:33,337
I knew it, you were
never a real mother.

316
00:18:33,421 --> 00:18:36,132
Even a three‐legged bitch
on the street can give birth

317
00:18:36,215 --> 00:18:38,134
and then abandon
her litter to die.

318
00:18:38,217 --> 00:18:39,885
[RIZA]
Now Come, Cain!

319
00:18:48,477 --> 00:18:49,937
[VALERIA]
So that's how it is.

320
00:18:50,021 --> 00:18:51,522
Are you prepared
for your demise?

321
00:18:51,606 --> 00:18:53,566
I suppose if you met
your end here,

322
00:18:53,649 --> 00:18:56,152
it would prevent Theresia's
tender heart from breaking.

323
00:18:56,235 --> 00:18:59,572
Quite the arrogant tone
from such a broken man!

324
00:19:08,873 --> 00:19:10,124
[REN gasps]

325
00:19:10,207 --> 00:19:11,667
[KEI] It appears one
of the swass‐tikas

326
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:13,586
has been opened elsewhere.

327
00:19:13,669 --> 00:19:17,131
Bey, most likely.
So that makes four.

328
00:19:17,214 --> 00:19:19,342
Five, once we're done here.

329
00:19:19,425 --> 00:19:22,511
When eight are opened,
my dream will come true!

330
00:19:22,595 --> 00:19:24,930
Lord Heydrich will
grant my wish.

331
00:19:25,014 --> 00:19:27,099
My family will return to me!

332
00:19:27,183 --> 00:19:28,184
[gasps]

333
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:30,311
[KEI]
He'll bring them back to life!

334
00:19:31,812 --> 00:19:33,981
[REN grunts] You think
he's gonna bring back

335
00:19:34,065 --> 00:19:35,566
your dead family?

336
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:40,404
You heard me! Impossible, right?
I know that's what you think!

337
00:19:40,488 --> 00:19:43,824
But what if I told you that
once you die, it isn't over.

338
00:19:43,908 --> 00:19:45,826
What would you do?

339
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:47,787
All it takes is the
wholesale slaughter

340
00:19:47,870 --> 00:19:50,581
of a few thousand people whose
names you never have to know.

341
00:19:50,665 --> 00:19:53,084
And you can be reunited
with the ones you love,

342
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:56,420
those torn from you. How could
you refuse such a great deal,

343
00:19:56,504 --> 00:19:58,756
when it's in front of you,
waiting to be taken?

344
00:19:58,839 --> 00:20:02,885
You'd be a fool too! That is
the miracle I long for.

345
00:20:02,968 --> 00:20:06,097
The gold beyond price that
Lord Heydrich will give me.

346
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:08,140
What else can I do?

347
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:11,185
[REN]
That's insane.

348
00:20:11,268 --> 00:20:12,603
[gasps]

349
00:20:12,687 --> 00:20:15,147
Do you realize how crazy
everything you're saying sounds?

350
00:20:15,231 --> 00:20:17,316
If they were really
that important to you,

351
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,819
if you loved them half
as much as you say,

352
00:20:19,902 --> 00:20:22,905
Would you really do such
horrible things in their name?

353
00:20:22,988 --> 00:20:24,949
Think about it. If you
have to pay for it

354
00:20:25,032 --> 00:20:28,202
with "a few thousand lives."
How in the hell can you tell me

355
00:20:28,285 --> 00:20:29,537
that it's "beyond price?"

356
00:20:29,620 --> 00:20:30,705
[KEI gasps]

357
00:20:30,788 --> 00:20:33,916
That's your gold?
Don't make me laugh!

358
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:36,544
Your "great deal"
isn't a bargain, Kei.

359
00:20:36,627 --> 00:20:40,631
It only lowers the value of all
the things you claim to love!

360
00:20:40,715 --> 00:20:47,179
[KEI] Shut up... Shut up!
Shut up! Shut up!

361
00:20:47,263 --> 00:20:48,931
[REN grunts]

362
00:20:50,891 --> 00:20:53,102
[grunts]

363
00:20:53,185 --> 00:20:59,066
[gasps] You're wrong.
What do you know about it?

364
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:01,569
And what the hell do
you know about me?!

365
00:21:01,652 --> 00:21:05,030
[ELEONORE] Disgusting.
You lose, little girl.

366
00:21:05,114 --> 00:21:06,240
[KEI shouts]

367
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:13,330
[ELEONORE] And you're quite
the orator, aren't you?

368
00:21:13,414 --> 00:21:16,167
That was an impressive speech.

369
00:21:31,056 --> 00:21:34,852
[ELEONORE] Now come,
bastard child of Karl Krafft.

370
00:21:34,935 --> 00:21:37,772
I will be the one to judge the
blade that has been offered up

371
00:21:37,855 --> 00:21:40,357
to Lord Heydrich.

372
00:21:40,441 --> 00:21:41,942
And if I find the
edge is dull,

373
00:21:42,026 --> 00:21:44,779
not even your
bones shall remain.

374
00:21:44,862 --> 00:21:49,825
♪

